    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. and what about communication? like, when you're in a high-stakes meeting with international clients, what's the most sophisticated way to speak and carry yourself to ensure you're taken seriously?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When it comes to communication, being clear, concise, and articulate is essential. Avoid using slang, colloquialisms, or overly casual language, as it can give the impression of being unprofessional. Instead, opt for a polished, measured tone, using formal language and avoiding filler words like \"um\" or \"ah.\" Also, be mindful of your body language, maintaining eye contact, sitting up straight, and using open, confident gestures. And, of course, a good command of the local language is always a plus, but if that's not possible, a neutral, well-rehearsed script can help you navigate complex conversations.",
